               <head>Gospel book;
                  late 13th c.</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>
                  
                  <msItem>
                     <title type="desc" key="work_12096">Gospel Book</title>
                     <msItem n="1">
                        <locus from="1r" to="64v">(fols. 1r–64v)</locus>
                        <note>Gospel of Matthew: the beginning is lost, so that the text now starts with
                           Mt 2:20.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="2">
                        <locus from="64v">(fol. 64v)</locus>
                        <note>Chapters list of the Gospel of Mark (end lost).</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="3">
                        <locus from="65r" to="103r">(fols. 65r–103r)</locus>
                        <note>Gospel of Mark: the beginning is lost, so that the text now starts with
                           Mk 1:31.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="4">
                        <locus from="103r" to="104v">(fols. 103r–104v)</locus>
                        <note>Chapters list for the Gospel of Luke. Fol. 105r is blank.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="5">
                        <locus from="105v" to="166r">(fols. 105v–166r)</locus>
                        <note>Gospel of Luke.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="6">
                        <locus from="166r">(fol. 166r)</locus>
                        <note>Colophon to the Gospel of Luke</note><colophon> Τὸ κατὰ Λουκᾶν ἅγιον εὐαγγέλιον ἐγράφη ἐν τῇ
                           Ῥώμῃ κατ’ ἐπιτροπὴν τοῦ ἁγίου ἀποστόλου Παύλου εἰς ὁμοίωμα μοσχαρίου.</colophon>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="7">
                        <locus from="166r" to="168r">(fols. 166r–168r)</locus>
                        <note> Chapters list for the Gospel of Luke. Fol. 168v is blank.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="8">
                        <locus from="169r" to="219v">(fols. 169r–219v)</locus>
                        <note>Gospel of John: the end is lost, so that the text now breaks off at Jn
                           21:18.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="9">
                        <locus from="220r" to="222v">(fols. 220r–222v)</locus>
                        <note>List of Gospel readings for the movable feast cycle, starting from
                           Easter Sunday.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="10">
                        <locus from="222v" to="224v">(fols. 222v–224v)</locus>
                        <note>List of Gospel readings for the fixed feast cycle, 1 September through
                           29 August (the end is probably lost).</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 225r–v, 225v–226r)</locus>
                        <note>Text on the added leaves: (225r-v) list of Gospel readings for the feast days of
                           various categories of saints (archangels, prophets, etc.) and for various occasions
                           (consecration of a church, earthquake, etc.), (225v–226r) note on the distribution
                           of Gospel readings: Τὸ δὲ κατὰ Ματθαῖον ἅγιον εὐαγγέλιον ἀναγινώσκεται ἀπὸ τῆς μετὰ
                           τῆς Πεντηκοστῆς δευτέρας ἤγουν τοῦ Ἁγίου Πνεύματος etc.: H. von Soden, <title>Die Schriften des Neuen Testaments in ihrer ältesten erreichbaren
                              Textgestalt</title> I.2 (Berlin 1906) 759.</note>
                     </msItem></msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <note>The lower text on the palimpsest ff. 225–226 is partly legible under ultra-violet
                        light. Still, I cannot identify it.</note>
                  </msItem>
