                  <handDesc hands="1">
                     <handNote> Produced by a single anonymous scribe who wrote Δόξα σοι Κ<ex>ύρι</ex>ε at the end of Luke’s
                        Gospel on f. 166r. – Ff. 225–226 were added to the manuscript in the fourteenth
                        century by an anonymous scribe B.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="headpiece">There are painted headbands on ff. 105v and 169r. Scribe B drew in black and red ink
                        an interlace headband on f. 225v.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions><p>Note in black ink in the outer margin of f. 69v: 1607 ναοπην τὸν χατζη […] εγω χαζη
                     Γερογης ο<lb/>μολογο του […] χαζη Λετερην γογορ.</p>  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notBefore="1500" notAfter="1700">
                        <p>Binding (perhaps sixteenth- or seventeenth-century) of blind-tooled brown leather
                           over wooded boards. The leather has been re-backed. The spine has been repaired and
                           the endbands, originally raised, are now trimmed down. Traces remains of two pins
                           and two leather thongs. There are no pastedowns and no endpapers.</p>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
